    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Wood</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 154.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 2, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>The Austro-Prussian armies have been
                            repulsed in their attacks on Dübbel and Frederica. Before the former
                            place the Prussian army must have lost heavily. His Majesty returned
                            yesterday from the army, pronouncing everything as satisfactory as
                            possible. The Danish government, after declining the first invitation to
                            the English conference, have finally accepted it on the basis of the
                            treaty of 1851-‘52, <hi rend="italic">or on some other condition equally
                                favorable</hi>. Prussia will insist on the virtual dismemberment of
                            Denmark; and England, to please her German sovereign, to avoid a war and
                            to preserve her material interest, will consent to it. I am glad to see
                            that this Danish-German question is beginning to be understood in the
                            United States.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to remain, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BRADFORD R. WOOD, <hi rend="italic">Minister
                                Resident.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
